%N A364270 a(n) = 2^^n + 3^^n, where ^^ indicates tetration.
%C A364270 a(4) has 3638334640025 digits and is too large to show here.
%C A364270 a(n) is prime for n = 0, 1, 2, 3, but it is not known if a(4) is prime.
%C A364270 From _Zhining Yang_, Feb 23 2026: (Start)
%C A364270 The least prime factor of a(4) is 21219553216129.
%C A364270 34276387 is a factor of a(k) for k >= 5.
%C A364270 4423 is a factor of a(k) for k >= 6.
%C A364270 42201151 is a factor of a(k) for k >= 7.
%C A364270 182668663 is a factor of a(k) for k >= 8. (End)
%H A364270 Zhihu, <a href="https://www.zhihu.com/question/512482114/answer/3410860527">Is 2^2^2^2+3^3^3^3 a prime number?</a> (in Chinese).
